From: tawc
Origin: own; candidate for upstreaming

With `-terminate <delay>`, the terminate timer is only (re)armed from
CloseDownClient: when a client disconnects and every remaining client
has marked itself disconnectable via XFixesSetClientDisconnectMode,
the server schedules its exit. A compositor's window manager client
sets that flag once, during its own startup.

That leaves a hole for socket-activated Xwayland: if the X11 client
whose connection triggered the activation dies before the WM client
has set its disconnect mode (e.g. SIGKILLed while Xwayland is still
starting up), its CloseDownClient runs while the WM still looks
non-disconnectable, so no timer is armed — and with no further client
ever connecting or disconnecting, the condition is never evaluated
again. Xwayland then idles forever with zero real clients, defeating
-terminate.

Fix: re-evaluate the terminate condition whenever a client changes its
disconnect mode. SetDispatchExceptionTimerIfIdle() arms the timer only
when every remaining client (including the caller) is disconnectable,
and SendConnSetup already cancels it when a real client completes its
handshake, so a healthy activating client keeps the server alive
exactly as before.
diff --git a/dix/dispatch.c b/dix/dispatch.c
index 7fc3a0554..2e5d18e06 100644
--- a/dix/dispatch.c
+++ b/dix/dispatch.c
@@ -452,6 +452,13 @@ ShouldDisconnectRemainingClients(void)
     return TRUE;
 }
 
+void
+SetDispatchExceptionTimerIfIdle(void)
+{
+    if (ShouldDisconnectRemainingClients())
+        SetDispatchExceptionTimer();
+}
+
 void
 EnableLimitedSchedulingLatency(void)
 {
diff --git a/dix/dix_priv.h b/dix/dix_priv.h
index 43eb0c706..fb5f93eca 100644
--- a/dix/dix_priv.h
+++ b/dix/dix_priv.h
@@ -24,6 +24,10 @@ extern char dispatchExceptionAtReset;
 extern int terminateDelay;
 extern Bool touchEmulatePointer;
 
+/* Arm the dispatch exception timer if every remaining client is
+ * disconnectable (XFixes client disconnect mode). */
+void SetDispatchExceptionTimerIfIdle(void);
+
 extern HWEventQueuePtr checkForInput[2];
 
 static inline _X_NOTSAN Bool
diff --git a/xfixes/disconnect.c b/xfixes/disconnect.c
index b3529af31..3e6b22f42 100644
--- a/xfixes/disconnect.c
+++ b/xfixes/disconnect.c
@@ -73,6 +73,15 @@ ProcXFixesSetClientDisconnectMode(ClientPtr client)
 
     pDisconnect->disconnect_mode = stuff->disconnect_mode;
 
+    /* The terminate timer is only re-evaluated when a client closes.
+     * If the last real client died before this client marked itself
+     * disconnectable (e.g. an Xwayland window manager setting the flag
+     * during startup while the socket-activating client is already
+     * gone), no further disconnect ever happens and the server lingers
+     * forever. Re-evaluate now that the set of disconnectable clients
+     * has changed. */
+    SetDispatchExceptionTimerIfIdle();
+
     return Success;
 }
 
